html(lang="en")
  head
    meta(charset="UTF-8")
    meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0")
    title wrap with tag | Docs
    link(rel="stylesheet" href="//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/materialize/1.0.0/css/materialize.min.css")
    link(rel="stylesheet" href="//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/9.13.1/styles/monokai.min.css")
    link(rel="stylesheet" href="//fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Noto+Serif")
    script(src="./js/script.js")
    script(src="//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/9.13.1/highlight.min.js")
    style.
      body {font-family: 'Noto Serif', serif;}
  body
    main.container.white
      header.row
        .col.s12.center
          h1.orange-text.darken-4 wrap-with-tag
      .row
        .col.s12
          p.flow-text.center A wrap-with-tag provides a simple function to wrap string with html.      
      section.row
        header.col.s12
          h5 This HTML is before excuting the Function <code>wrapWithTag</code>.
        .col.s12
          pre
            code.html.
              &lt;p>Company - FizzBuzz&lt/p>
              &lt;p>!!company!!&lt/p>
      section.row
        header.col.s12
          h5 Execute the function after loading the DOM.
        .col.s12
          pre
            code.js.
              wrapWithTag({
                regexp: /(company)/gi,
                className: 'font',
                tagName: 'em'
              })
      section.row
        header.col.s12
          h5 This HTML is after excuting the Function <code>wrapWithTag</code>.
          p Strings that match the regular expression are wrapped with html <code>&lt;em class="font">&lt;/em></code>
        .col.s12
          pre
            code.html.
              &lt;p>&lt;em class="font">Company&lt;/em> - FizzBuzz&lt/p>
              &lt;p>!!&lt;em class="font">company&lt;/em>!!&lt/p>
